headline: How The Texas Capital Bancshares (TCBI) Story Is Shifting As Analysts Rework Price Targets
summary: The fair value estimate for Texas Capital Bancshares has been revised slightly higher, from US$105.62 to US$105.79, reflecting a very small adjustment in the latest model. Analysts link this fine tuning to updated views on earnings power, balance sheet trends, and how regional bank fundamentals might shape upcoming earnings updates. headline: Private-Credit BDC Market Offers a Choice: Cheap Public Funds or Richer Private Ones
summary: Private credit lending involves high-rate debt issued to private companies that often carry yields of around 10%.  The average redemption among nine leading private funds was close to 5% of net asset value, according to  Moody’s  Some BDCs exceeded that 5% cap and met the full redemption requests.  The private funds also saw sizable inflows in the fourth quarter that in the case of Blackstone Private Credit Fund (Bcred), the largest private fund, exceeded redemptions.

headline: Casella Waste Systems (CWST) Narrative Shifts As Integration Progress Meets Mixed Street Expectations
summary: Casella Waste Systems has seen its fair value estimate trimmed slightly to US$114.90 from US$115.33 per share, a small move that still matters if you are watching the name closely. Around the Street, research updates range from the Jefferies upgrade to Buy with a US$120 target to more cautious trims to about US$110, reflecting different views on integration progress and execution risk.
